notesStmt.note: Two owner's notes, one dated 1281 A.H. (1864 or 1865 CE) (f. 1r).

msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Dictionary of sufi and philosophical terms.

author.persName: Jurjānī, ʻAlī ibn Muḥammad, al-Sayyid al-Sharīf, 1340-1413

respStmt.persName: ʻAbd al-Razzāq ibn Ḥusayn Afandī, active 1864

respStmt.name: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

supportDesc.extent: 130 leaves : 145 x 100 (95 x 50) bound to 145 x 105 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

binding.p: Mostly disbound; covers of brown leather over thin pasteboard with flap (Type II); blind-tooled frame of double parallel lines and blind-stamped central mandorla; title on bottom edge in black ink.

origin.p: Copy completed in 1052 A.H. (1643 of 1643 CE) by Muḥammad ibn Muṣṭafá al-Qarahʹfaryahʹvī (Qarafaryavī) (f. 130v).

history.provenance: Gift of Solomon L. Skoss to the library of the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (library bookplate front inside cover).
Formerly owned by ʻAbd al-Razzāq ibn Ḥusayn Afandī in 1864 or 5 (note in ink, f. 1r).
Formerly owned by Aḥmad ibn ʻUmar Afandī (undated note in ink, f. 1r).
Formerly owned by the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (library bookplate inside front cover).

surface.n: Inside back cover flap open to show design
Back cover flap open to show design
Fore edge flap closed, inside front cover
